ed ice-photochemistry residue", "inputs": ["mol_024"], "outputs": ["mol_016"], "environment": "Biochemical", "agents": ["aqueous workup"], "conditions": {"temperature": "warm-up / hydrolysis workup", "pressure": "ambient after deposition stage", "catalyst": "none", "aqueous": "true", "other": "hydrolyzed residue analyzed for amino acids"}, "mechanism": "Amino-acid release and identification from complex photochemical residue, represented here as serine recovery.", "reasoning": "This follows the retained interpretation of SER-R6 that serine is obtained after hydrolysis/workup of irradiated ice residues. Because the validated bundle does not give a numeric yield or a more detailed isolated preparative step, this is represented conservatively as serine recovery from the residue pool (Mu\u00f1oz Caro et al., 2002; Elsila et al., 2007; Nuevo et al., 2008; serine_reaction_table.csv)."}, {"id": "rxn_014", "name": "Spark-discharge synthesis of amino acid mixture containing serine and glycine", "inputs": ["mol_008", "mol_018", "mol_019", "mol_002"], "outputs": ["mol_016", "mol_022"], "environment": "Surface", "agents": ["TiO2 (anatase/rutile)", "montmorillonite (clay)"], "conditions": {"temperature": "bulk apparatus mild; local spark/plasma hot", "pressure": "not extracted", "catalyst": "spark discharge; mineral collection support imposed by network constraints", "aqueous": "true", "other": "reduced atmosphere simulation with condensed aqueous traps"}, "mechanism": "Electrical discharge through reduced gas mixtures forms amino-acid product mixtures in condensates, including serine and glycine.", "reasoning": "This is SER-R7. The validated report states that Yu et al. (2014) found serine in discharge condensates, though no absolute serine yield was extracted. Glycine is also included because Miller-Urey-type mixtures commonly contain it and it is needed to connect the validated low-confidence hydroxymethylation route family retained in the serine bundle (Yu et al., 2014; seri