\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"cryogenic irradiation then warm-up\",\n        \"pressure\": \"vacuum / low pressure during ice irradiation\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"UV/VUV photons\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"false\",\n        \"other\": \"ice analogs followed by hydrolysis/workup; environment retained from astrochemical literature family\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"UV/VUV processing of simple ice mixtures generates amino-acid-containing residues that release serine upon hydrolysis and warm-up.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Retained route SER-R6 explicitly identifies UV/VUV-irradiated H2O/CH3OH/NH3/CO(\u00b1CO2) ice mixtures as producing residues that yield serine after hydrolysis. Exact numeric yield and all cryogenic parameters were not extracted in the validated bundle, but the route family itself is retained and literature-supported (Mu\u00f1oz Caro et al., 2002; Elsila et al., 2007; Nuevo et al., 2008).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_012\",\n      \"name\": \"Formaldehyde plus glycine hydroxymethylation concept to serine\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_017\", \"mol_003\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_018\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Biochemical\",\n      \"agents\": [\"null\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"not established from accessible primary text\",\n        \"pressure\": \"ambient\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"none securely established\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"formaldehyde-bearing surface waters / evaporative pools; low-confidence contested route\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Conceptual hydroxymethylation of glycine by formaldehyde supplies the beta-carbon of serine.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Retained route SER-R8 is explicitly the lowest-confidence route in the validated corpus. It is included because historical and source-list evidence supports the conceptual chemistry that formaldehyde can supply the beta-carbon of serine, but the report stresses that modern abiotic serine-specific conditions and yields were not securely extracted. This edge is therefore retained as contested and low-confidence, not as a strong validated route (Shemin & Rittenberg, 1950; Okafor et al., 2017 source-list context; JACS Au 2024 DOI:10.1021/jacsau.4c00685; serine_s6_analysis.md).\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"pathways\": [\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P1\",\n      \"name\": \"Validated Green aminonitrile to hydrolysis route\",\n      \"description\": \"Best-supported serine-specific route: glycolaldehyde enters warm formamide Strecker-like chemistry to form serine nitrile, which is then hydrolyzed in an unresolved alkaline aqueous release step.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_007\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_004\", \"mol_010\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P2\",\n      \"name\": \"Validated protected reservoir route through N-formylserine nitrile\",\n      \"description\": \"Green formamide chemistry forms serine nitrile from glycolaldehyde and then converts it to the strongly supported protected reservoir N-formylserine nitrile before alkaline hydrolysis to serine.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_006\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_010\", \"mol_011\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P3\",\n      \"name\": \"Cyanosulfidic precursor pool to serine nitrile to serine\",\n      \"description\": \"Patel-type cyanosulfidic photoredox supplies glycolonitrile and related precursors that feed a serine nitrile pool, followed by hydrolysis to serine.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_002\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_007\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_014\", \"mol_010\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P4\",\n      \"name\": \"Cyanosulfidic precursor pool into Green Strecker chemistry\",\n      \"description\": \"Cyanosulfidic photoredox generates glycolaldehyde, which then follows the Green formamide route through serine nitrile and N-formylserine nitrile before release.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_002\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_006\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_004\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_011\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P5\",\n      \"name\": \"Hydrothermal feedstock to surface glycolaldehyde then Green route\",\n      \"description\": \"Speculative hydrothermal C1 reduction feeds formaldehyde into surface precursor chemistry, producing glycolaldehyde that enters the Green serine nitrile route and alkaline release.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_007\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_003\", \"mol_004\", \"mol_010\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P6\",\n      \"name\": \"Hydrothermal feedstock to cyanosulfidic precursor supply to protected reservoir\",\n      \"description\": \"Hydrothermal background feedstock formaldehyde is transferred to surface cyanosulfidic precursor chemistry, then into the Green serine nitrile and N-formylserine nitrile network.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_002\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_006\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_003\", \"mol_004\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_011\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P7\",\n      \"name\": \"Warm formamide branch route via MgCl2-assisted FoSer-CN formation\",\n      \"description\": \"Serine nitrile enters the MgCl2-assisted branch network in formamide, one branch returning to N-formylserine nitrile which can then be hydrolyzed to serine.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_006\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_010\", \"mol_011\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"name\": \"Direct spark-discharge serine occurrence route\",\n      \"description\": \"Reduced-atmosphere spark discharge directly yields serine in complex product mixtures collected in aqueous traps.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_018\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n      \"name\": \"Ice-UV hydrolytic residue route\",\n      \"description\": \"Astrochemical ice irradiation followed by warm-up and hydrolysis yields serine as part of the amino-acid residue inventory.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_011\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_018\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n      \"name\": \"Contested glycine-formaldehyde hydroxymethylation route\",\n      \"description\": \"Low-confidence conceptual route in which glycine reacts with formaldehyde to supply the beta-carbon of serine in aqueous surface settings.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_012\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_017\", \"mol_003\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"hub_molecules\": [\"mol_003\", \"mol_004\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_011\", \"mol_018\"],\n  \"convergence_points\": [\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_004\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_002\", \"rxn_009\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_003\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_010\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_008\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_004\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_007\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_011\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_004\", \"rxn_005\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_006\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_003\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_001\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_002\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_012\", \"rxn_011\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_018\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_010\", \"rxn_011\", \"rxn_012\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": []\n    }\n  ]\n}", "parsed_response": {"target_molecule": "Serine", "overall_strategy": "This network is centered on the literature-supported serine-precursor system rather than claiming a fully quantified free-serine synthesis. The core validated hub is serine nitrile, forme