nce >= 0.9\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: Serine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: This network is centered on the literature-supported serine-precursor system rather than claiming a fully quantified free-serine synthesis. The core validated hub is serine nitrile, formed most strongly from glycolaldehyde under warm formamide Strecker-like conditions, then converted to N-formylserine nitrile in formamide and only subsequently subjected to alkaline aqueous processing to plausibly release serine-related products including serine. To satisfy environmental interconnection while remaining faithful to the provided serine literature, hydrothermal chemistry is restricted to speculative background supply of simple feedstocks already emphasized in the report as entering surface chemistry, and all serine-specific productive chemistry is placed in surface/formamide, cyanosulfidic, atmospheric discharge, ice-photochemical, and biochemical rehydration contexts explicitly documented in the literature. The target serine is therefore represented as arising through multiple literature-grounded routes, with the final hydrolysis step marked as unresolved in quantitative yield.\n\nMOLECULES (20 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CO2 (carbon dioxide) [starting]\n  - mol_002: H2 (hydrogen) [starting]\n  - mol_003: CH2O (formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_004: C2H4O2 (glycolaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CHN (HCN) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CH3NO (formamide) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: H3N (ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_008: NaCN (sodium cyanide) [starting]\n  - mol_009: NH4Cl (ammonium chloride) [starting]\n  - mol_010: C3H6N2O (serine nitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_011: C4H6N2O2 (N-formylserine nitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_012: C4H4N2O2 (N-formyldehydroalanine nitrile) [intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C4H6N2O2 (Fo(beta-formylamino)alanine nitrile) [intermediate]\n